  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "FMCG Sales Merchandiser",
  "description": "<p>Be part of a high-energy team that brings leading FMCG brands to life at the point of sale and help shape the consumer shopping experience!</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></u></p>\n<p>· Execute in-store merchandising of FMCG products by arranging, presenting, and refreshing displays to align with brand guidelines and promotional calendars.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>· Build and maintain positive working relationships with retail store personnel, supervisors, and key account managers to ensure smooth execution of merchandising plans.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>· Monitor stock levels on shelves and in the storeroom, coordinating timely replenishment to prevent out-of-stock situations.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>· Set up promotional displays, point-of-sale materials, and ensure pricing is accurate and visible during campaigns and seasonal pushes.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>· Report on market intelligence, including competitor activities, shelf share, shopper behavior, and product feedback.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>· Achieve sales and merchandising performance targets by implementing effective product placement and visibility strategies.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u><strong>Requirements</strong></u></p>\n<p>· At least 2–3 years of experience in the FMCG industry, with a strong background in retail, sales, or merchandising.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>· Excellent communication and negotiation skills with the ability to influence at the store level.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>· Highly motivated and able to work independently while traveling to multiple store locations within assigned territory.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>· Physically capable of handling stock (up to 20kg) and standing for long hours during store visits and product setups.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>· Familiarity with planograms, in-store execution standards, and sales reporting tools is a plus.</p>",
